    <h2>5.1.2 Reaction profiles</h2>
    <p>
        - Chemical reactions can occur only when reacting particles collide with
        each other and with sufficient energy.<br>
        - The minimum amount of energy that particles must have to react is called
        the activation energy.<br>
        - Reaction profiles can be used to show the relative energies of reactants
        and products, the activation energy and the overall energy change of a reaction.
    </p>
